	"achievement.noLife.name": "Absolutely Jobless",
	"achievement.noLife.description": "Waste your life away for no reason. You have been branded, marked permanently.",
	"achievement.rarePolarizeSuccess.name": "Reverse Russian Roulette ",
	"achievement.rarePolarizeSuccess.description": "You know this skill is risky, especially when it's a fresh batch of bullets, but miraculously you made it work.",
	// Use Polarize when there are 6 bullets in the chamber, and not inflate yourself.
	"achievement.eliminateByAssault.name": "Quick Draw",
	"achievement.eliminateByAssault.description": "A person on the verge of defeat must be dealt with swiftly... using a more direct method.",
	// Eliminate a player via Assault.
	"achievement.findCameraman.name": "Lights, Camera, Action!",
	"achievement.findCameraman.description": "Have you seen the cameraman before?",
	// Meet Cobalt. (1/128 probability)
	"achievement.winByYourself.name": "True Singleplayer",
	"achievement.winByYourself.description": "\"If you know yourself, you need not fear the result of a hundred battles.\" - The Art of War, probably.",
	// Win a game against yourself (All players are human and only one player uses a skill)
	"achievement.winAgainstStrategicCPUs.name": "Mind Games",
	"achievement.winAgainstStrategicCPUs.description": "Not gonna lie the bots aren't very smart either, but seeing everyone raging over these freaks, nice job.",
	// Win a game with every CPU set to its highest skill level.
	"achievement.nineTwentyOne.name": "9 Deaths with 21 Injured",
	"achievement.nineTwentyOne.description": "You seein' this? That's the type of image that gets worse when you see 'em.",
	// Play at exactly 9:21 PM, a random stupid image will flash on-screen briefly.
	"achievement.exportCharacterProject.name": "Utilizer",
	"achievement.exportCharacterProject.description": "Construct your own vessel using the Migrational Order Directive utility program.",
	// Export your first character creator project.
	
	"achievementsMenu.title": "Your achievements",
	"achievementsMenu.description": "Select an achievement to view its details and completion status.",
	"achievementsMenu.resetProgress": "Reset Progress",
	
	"achievementToast.title": "Achievement Unlocked!",
	
	"resetAchievementMenu.prompt": "Confirm your reset of\n%1?\nThis action is irreversible.",
	
	// If the language's script can be written vertically, set this string to false
	"galleryMainMenu.envelope.rotateText": "true",
	// Context: According to Snowyboi, there are different versions of Goobers, one being Slime Goobers, and one labelled "???".
	// The way I interpret this is like, them having races or something
	"galleryMainMenu.envelope.goober.description": "First seen in the original game, the Goobers jump into action with a new coat of paint! They have become the go-to character to be featured in countless remakes and fanart alike.\n\nAs for why and how they joined the game, no one knows! Actors? Hostages? Sell-outs? Lots of theories are out there! Not much is known about their biology, but it has been confirmed that they have been classified into several races, ranging from Goobers composed entirely out of slime to R»EDA©±ED§²½\n\nGoober is a species created by Snowyboi.",
	// Context: Literally no lore implication. He's just here for the sake of being here lol
	"galleryMainMenu.envelope.asimo.description": "Harnessing his electric powers, Asimo jolts into Inflation Roulette claiming to \"have some fun\".\n\nWe don't know how he got here, and we totally have no connections with him, other than he's a wolf, he's the Manager's playtester for his stupid Friday Night Funkin' mod, and he's the winner of an art raffle to be added to the game as a character for the Example Addon.\n\nAsimo is a guest character owned by WolfKylis.",
	// Context: You can say the reason they're here is nepotism? They're just a partner with the Manager's lab-grown assistant
	// that agrees to join that's it.
	"galleryMainMenu.envelope.shibanou.description": "Last name Nou; first name Shiba. Hailing from a mysterious planet, this cat-like creature is ready to blast someone. Their Chinese name can be interpreted as \"Zero Ten Eight\", derived from the nuclear site they landed on in Beijing.\n\nSpending the first few years of their life scouring to different places to live, they eventually founded themself inside of The Manager's garage. The man adopted them as his secondary assistant and soon found themself in love with the primary assistant (lab-grown btw, ew). With no apparent reason other than to show-off in front of their boyfriend, they joined the game to show off their hidden abilities.\n\nShibanou is a character owned by NicklySuffer, made prior to the development of Inflation Roulette Reloaded.",
	// Context: The Manager and Shitfucks partnered, and selected Chester as their ambassador or something.
	"galleryMainMenu.envelope.chester.description": "As the lead barista of a coffee shop, he was forced to play this game as an ambassador for the company. With his poor academic results and his uncharismatic personality, his dream of prosperity and wealth is yet to be in reach.\n\nHis daily work involves making oversweetened beverages for horny customers. Some say the drinks have an \"expansive\" effect, which has grabbed the attention of several food safety agents. However, due to some capitalist bullshit, warnings from the food department went nowhere.\n\nChester is a character owned by NicklySuffer, made prior to the development of Inflation Roulette Reloaded.",
	"galleryMainMenu.envelope.dev": "Developer Art",
	"galleryMainMenu.envelope.dev.description": "A collection of concept art, sketches, and unused assets made by the developers and other artists.\n\nangry           bird",
	"galleryMainMenu.envelope.community": "Community Art",
	"galleryMainMenu.envelope.community.description": "A collection of fanart drawn by the developers' friends and the community.",
	"galleryEntryMenu.viewFullImage": "View Full Image",
	
